Rust has fine-grained memory management, but is automatically managed once created. Mutability propagates deeply into owned types struct A { b: B } struct B { c: usize } fn main() { let mut a = A { b: B { c: 2 } }; a.b.c = 3; a.b = B { c: 4 }; a = A { b: B { c: 5 } }; let frozen = a; frozen.b.c = 4; // error!
}

name = "my_lib"
version = "0.1.0"
authors = ["Azriel Hoh"] [dependencies]
uuid = "0.5.0" [dev-dependencies]
time = "0.1.37"
